    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="92"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d92">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2" type="from"
                            >Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d92fn1">Apparently sent via military channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-03">3 November
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FormerNavalPerson1">Former Naval Person</gloss> to President
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> personal and most secret
                    Number 488. Your number 406.<note n="2" xml:id="d92fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_62">p. 62</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>I and the British Staffs will await you in Cairo on 22nd.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>We think it necessary that the British and United States Staffs should
                        consult together before any triple conference with the Russians take[s]
                        place, and that when it takes place there should be a responsible Russian
                        delegation and not a mere observer. I should be grateful if you would let me
                        know whether you agree with this.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
